This paper is primarily focused on reinforcement learning (RL) and representation learning, which are both subfields of machine learning. The paper introduces the concept of a DeepMDP, which is a parameterized latent space model that is trained via the minimization of two tractable losses. This suggests that the paper is likely to be categorized under cs.LG (Machine Learning) or cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). 

The paper also explores the use of metrics and connects its results to prior work in the bisimulation literature, which suggests that it may also be categorized under cs.CL (Computation and Language). Additionally, the paper discusses experiments on the Atari 2600 domain, which involves image processing, and thus may also be categorized under cs.CV (Computer Vision). Finally, the paper deals with RL tasks, which are often related to control systems, suggesting that it may also be categorized under cs.SY (Systems and Control). 

Overall, the most likely categories are cs.LG and cs.AI, followed by cs.CL, cs.CV, and cs.SY.
